Unseen \Un*seen"\, a. 1. Not seen or discovered. [1913 Webster]
2. Unskilled; inexperienced. [Obs.] --Clarendon. [1913 Webster]
unseen adj 1: not seen or perceived; "unseen natural resources" 2: not observed [syn: {unobserved}] n : a belief that there is a realm controlled by a divine spirit [syn: {spiritual world}]
